I bought a couch and made the mistake of paying in advance. These people will be very nice while you're shopping, but after you've paid or signed, they're done being helpful. They will waste your time and make you regret stepping through the door. 

They:
failed to schedule a delivery;
made me insist upon canceling before they agreed to deliver on time;
failed to add the item to the driver's manifest even when it was finally scheduled;
gave me the run-around to avoid having me cancel.

When all was said and done, the sales associate, Farah, told me he would talk to his manager and call me back in 15 minutes. I knew he was lying, so I called Discover and had them dispute the charge. I'm glad I did, I am now three hours into that 15 minute window.

I highly recommend going elsewhere.
